@startuml CI-CD Deployment Pipeline
!include <C4/C4_Component>

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam ArrowColor #333333

title Healthcare Insurance Multi-Agent AI Platform\nCI/CD Production Deployment Pipeline\n(GitHub Actions - Automated Deployment)

|GitHub|
start

:Developer pushes code\nto main branch;
note right
  **Trigger Events:**
  • Push to main
  • Pull request merge
  • Manual workflow_dispatch
  • Scheduled: Daily 2 AM
end note

|GitHub Actions - Security Scan Job|
:Checkout code;

fork
  :**Secret Scanning**\n(GitGuardian);
  note right
    Detect exposed:
    • API keys
    • Database passwords
    • Azure credentials
    • SSH keys
  end note
fork again
  :**SAST - Static Analysis**\n(SonarQube);
  note right
    Code quality:
    • Code smells
    • Security vulnerabilities
    • Code coverage
    • Duplicate code
  end note
fork again
  :**Dependency Scanning**\n(Snyk, Dependabot);
  note right
    Check for:
    • CVE vulnerabilities
    • Outdated packages
    • License compliance
    • Supply chain risks
  end note
fork again
  :**Container Scanning**\n(Trivy);
  note right
    Scan images for:
    • OS vulnerabilities
    • Application CVEs
    • Misconfigurations
    • Secrets in layers
  end note
end fork

if (Security scan passed?) then (yes)
  :✓ Security approved;
else (no)
  :✗ Block deployment;
  stop
endif

|GitHub Actions - Build & Test Job|
:Run unit tests\n(pytest, Jest);
note right
  **Test Coverage:**
  • Unit tests: 500+ tests
  • Integration tests: 150+ tests
  • E2E tests: 50+ tests
  
  **Coverage Target:** >85%
  **Time:** ~15 minutes
end note

fork
  :**Backend Tests**\n(Python/FastAPI);
  note right
    Test suites:
    • Agent logic
    • RAG pipeline
    • API endpoints
    • Database models
  end note
fork again
  :**Frontend Tests**\n(React/Jest);
  note right
    Test suites:
    • Component tests
    • Integration tests
    • Snapshot tests
  end note
fork again
  :**LLM Tests**\n(Eval framework);
  note right
    Test:
    • Prompt regression
    • Output validation
    • Hallucination detection
    • Tool calling accuracy
  end note
end fork

if (All tests passed?) then (yes)
  :✓ Tests passed;
else (no)
  :✗ Block deployment;
  stop
endif

:Build Docker images;
note right
  **Images Built:**
  • clinical-agent:v2.3.1
  • intake-agent:v1.8.2
  • policy-agent:v2.1.0
  • fraud-agent:v1.9.5
  • decision-agent:v2.0.3
  
  **Build Optimization:**
  • Multi-stage builds
  • Layer caching
  • Minimal base images
  
  **Time:** ~10 minutes
end note

|GitHub Actions - Push to ACR Job|
:Tag images with\nversion + SHA;
note right
  **Tagging Strategy:**
  • v2.3.1 (semantic version)
  • sha-abc1234 (git commit)
  • latest (most recent)
  • staging (for staging env)
  
  **Example:**
  acrhealthcare.azurecr.io/
    clinical-agent:v2.3.1
end note

:Push to Azure Container Registry;
note right
  **Registry:**
  acrhealthcareprod.azurecr.io
  
  **Security:**
  • Admin account disabled
  • Service principal auth
  • Image signing enabled
  • Vulnerability scanning
  
  **Retention:** 90 days for old tags
end note

:Scan images in ACR\n(Azure Defender);
note right
  **Defender for Containers:**
  • Continuous scanning
  • CVE detection
  • Compliance checks
  • Alert on HIGH/CRITICAL
end note

if (ACR scan clean?) then (yes)
  :✓ Images approved;
else (no)
  :✗ Block deployment;
  stop
endif

|GitHub Actions - Deploy to Staging|
:Update Helm values\n(staging.yaml);
note right
  **Staging Config:**
  • replicas: 2 (vs 10 prod)
  • resources: 50% of prod
  • ingress: staging.healthcare.internal
  • database: staging DB
end note

:Helm upgrade\nstaging release;
note right
  **Helm Command:**
  helm upgrade healthcare-platform ./charts \
    --namespace healthcare-staging \
    --values staging.yaml \
    --wait --timeout 10m
  
  **Deployment Strategy:** RollingUpdate
  **Max Unavailable:** 25%
  **Max Surge:** 25%
end note

:Wait for rollout\ncomplete;
note right
  **Health Checks:**
  • Readiness probe: /health
  • Liveness probe: /healthz
  • Startup probe: /startup
  
  **Timeout:** 10 minutes
end note

:Run smoke tests\non staging;
note right
  **Smoke Tests:**
  • API health check
  • Database connectivity
  • Agent initialization
  • Critical user flows
  
  **Time:** ~5 minutes
end note

if (Staging tests passed?) then (yes)
  :✓ Staging validated;
else (no)
  :✗ Rollback staging;
  stop
endif

|GitHub Actions - Deploy to Production|
:⏸️ Wait for manual approval;
note right
  **Approval Gate:**
  • Environment: production
  • Approvers: 
    - Tech Lead
    - DevOps Lead
    - Product Owner (1 required)
  
  **Review Checklist:**
  ✓ All tests passed
  ✓ Security scans clean
  ✓ Staging deployment successful
  ✓ Change ticket approved
end note

if (Approved?) then (yes)
  :✓ Deployment approved;
else (no)
  :✗ Deployment cancelled;
  stop
endif

fork
  |Primary Region - East US 2|
  :Update Helm values\n(prod-east.yaml);
  
  :Canary deployment\n(10% traffic);
  note right
    **Canary Strategy:**
    • Step 1: 10% traffic (5 min)
    • Monitor: error rate, latency
    • Step 2: 50% traffic (10 min)
    • Monitor: business metrics
    • Step 3: 100% traffic
  end note
  
  :Monitor canary metrics;
  note right
    **Success Criteria:**
    • Error rate < 1%
    • P95 latency < 3s
    • No critical alerts
    
    **Auto-rollback if:**
    • Error rate > 5%
    • P95 latency > 10s
    • Critical alerts fired
  end note
  
  if (Canary successful?) then (yes)
    :Promote to 100%;
  else (no)
    :Auto-rollback;
    stop
  endif
  
  :Helm upgrade production\n(East US 2);
  note right
    **Production Deployment:**
    helm upgrade healthcare-platform ./charts \
      --namespace healthcare-prod \
      --values prod-east.yaml \
      --wait --timeout 15m
    
    **Replicas:**
    • clinical-agent: 10
    • intake-agent: 8
    • policy-agent: 5
    • fraud-agent: 6
    • decision-agent: 4
  end note
  
  :Verify production\nhealth (East);

fork again
  |Secondary Region - West US 2|
  :Wait 10 minutes\n(stagger deployment);
  
  :Update Helm values\n(prod-west.yaml);
  
  :Helm upgrade production\n(West US 2);
  note right
    **Secondary Region:**
    • Same configuration as East
    • Traffic Manager: Priority 2
    • Active-Active setup
    • Auto-failover enabled
  end note
  
  :Verify production\nhealth (West);
end fork

|GitHub Actions - Post-Deployment|
:Run integration tests\non production;
note right
  **Integration Tests:**
  • End-to-end PA workflow
  • API contract tests
  • Performance tests
  • Multi-region failover
  
  **Time:** ~10 minutes
end note

if (Integration tests passed?) then (yes)
  :✓ Deployment successful;
else (no)
  :✗ Trigger rollback;
  |Rollback Procedure|
  fork
    :Rollback East US 2;
    note right
      helm rollback healthcare-platform \
        --namespace healthcare-prod
      
      Reverts to previous release
      Time: ~2 minutes
    end note
  fork again
    :Rollback West US 2;
  end fork
  stop
endif

:Update deployment status;
note right
  **Status Updates:**
  • GitHub deployment status
  • Azure DevOps board
  • Slack notification
  • Email to stakeholders
end note

:Tag GitHub release;
note right
  **Release Tag:**
  • v2.3.1
  • Changelog auto-generated
  • Release notes
  • Deployment timestamp
end note

|Notification|
fork
  :Slack notification\n#deployments;
  note right
    **Message:**
    🚀 Production deployment successful
    
    Version: v2.3.1
    Regions: East US 2, West US 2
    Deployer: @john.doe
    Duration: 45 minutes
    
    Tests: ✅ All passed
    Health: ✅ All green
  end note
fork again
  :Email to stakeholders;
fork again
  :Azure DevOps work item\nupdate;
end fork

stop

note right
  **Deployment Metrics:**
  • Frequency: 3-5 per week
  • Success rate: 98.5%
  • Average duration: 45 minutes
  • Rollback rate: 1.5%
  • MTTR (rollback): 5 minutes
  
  **SLO:**
  • Deployment success: >95%
  • Zero downtime: 100%
  • Rollback time: <10 minutes
end note

@enduml
